cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.FL

This paper deals with an extension of properties and assertions in (C)LP, which is a subfield of programming languages (PL). The extension is specifically for higher-order constructs, which involve the manipulation of functions and predicates, making it relevant to the logic in computer science (LO) subfield. The paper also discusses error detection and program validation, which are topics in software engineering (SE) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper proposes syntax and semantics for the extended assertions, which is related to formal languages (FL).
